February 2, 2015

We will consider several variables from the AddHealth data set. Looking in the code book for H1SU1 suggest responses of 6, 8, and 9 should be recoded to NA.

library(PDS)
xtabs(~H1SU1, data = AddHealth)
H1SU1
   0    1    6    8    9 
5614  821   46   22    1 
AddHealth$H1SU1[AddHealth$H1SU1==6 | AddHealth$H1SU1==8 | AddHealth$H1SU1==9] <- NA
xtabs(~H1SU1, data = AddHealth)
H1SU1
   0    1    6    8    9 
5614  821    0    0    0 
AddHealth$H1SU1 <- factor(AddHealth$H1SU1, labels = c("No", "Yes"))[, drop = TRUE]
xtabs(~H1SU1, data = AddHealth)
H1SU1
  No  Yes 
5614  821 
summary(AddHealth$H1SU1)
  No  Yes NA's 
5614  821   69 
freq(AddHealth$H1SU1)

AddHealth$H1SU1 
      Frequency Percent Valid Percent
No         5614  86.316         87.24
Yes         821  12.623         12.76
NA's         69   1.061              
Total      6504 100.000        100.00
freq(AddHealth$H1SU1, main = "Did you ever seriously think about committing suicide?", col = c("skyblue", "gray"))

AddHealth$H1SU1 
      Frequency Percent Valid Percent
No         5614  86.316         87.24
Yes         821  12.623         12.76
NA's         69   1.061              
Total      6504 100.000        100.00
ggplot(data = AddHealth, aes(x = H1SU1, fill = H1SU1)) + 
  geom_bar() + 
  labs(title = "Did you ever seriously think about committing suicide?", x = "") +
  theme_bw()

Question H1SU2 asks the 821 repondents from H1SU1 “how many times did you attempt suicide?” Response of a 7 should be recoded to NA.

xtabs(~H1SU2, data = AddHealth)
H1SU2
   0    1    2    3    4    6    7    8 
 587  131   64   10   25    3 5683    1 
AddHealth$H1SU2[AddHealth$H1SU2==7] <- NA
xtabs(~H1SU2, data = AddHealth)
H1SU2
  0   1   2   3   4   6   7   8 
587 131  64  10  25   3   0   1 
AddHealth$H1SU2 <- factor(AddHealth$H1SU2)[, drop = TRUE]
xtabs(~H1SU2, data = AddHealth)
H1SU2
  0   1   2   3   4   6   8 
587 131  64  10  25   3   1 
AddHealth$H1SU2 <- factor(AddHealth$H1SU2, labels = c("0 times", "1 time", "2 or 3 times", "4 or 5 times", ">= 6 times", "refused", "don't know"))
summary(AddHealth$H1SU2)

     refused   don't know         NA's

NAS <- sum(xtabs(~H1SU2, data = AddHealth)[2:5])  # number that actually attempted suicide

ggplot(data = AddHealth, aes(x = H1SU2)) + 
  geom_bar(fill = "maroon") + 
  labs(title = "How many times did you actually attempt suicide?", x= "") +

ggplot(data = na.omit(AddHealth[ , "H1SU2", drop = FALSE]), aes(x = H1SU2)) + 
  geom_bar(fill = "plum") + 
  labs(title = "How many times did you actually attempt suicide?", x = "") +
  theme_bw()

  labs(title = "How many times did you actually attempt suicide?", x = "") +
  theme_bw()

Question H1SU3 asks of the 230 that attempted suicide if they had to be treated by either a nurse or doctor. The response of 7 should be recoded to NA.

AddHealth$H1SU3[AddHealth$H1SU3 == 7] <- NA
AddHealth$H1SU3 <- factor(AddHealth$H1SU3, labels = c("No", "Yes"))[, drop = TRUE]
xtabs(~H1SU3, data = AddHealth)
